Description:
    Generate a migration that installs 4-op PostgreSQL Row-Level Security (RLS) policies
    on a single table. Used to backfill RLS on tables added after the initial RLS migration,
    or to equip a brand-new business table with proper write protection.

    The generated migration idempotently:
      1. DROPs any legacy `FOR ALL` policy (named <table>_version_policy)
      2. DROPs any existing <table>_{select,insert,update,delete}_policy
      3. ENABLEs + FORCEs RLS on the table
      4. CREATEs 4 policies:
         - SELECT: allow baseline (data_version='0') OR current session
         - INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE: reject baseline unless app.baseline_loading='on'
           AND only allow current session (data_version = current_setting('app.data_version'))

    Prerequisites:
      - The table must already have a `data_version` column (added by rails g model).
      - The project must already have the base RLS migrations applied
        (enable_rls_on_business_tables + split_rls_policies_by_operation).
        If not, run `rake validator:lint_schema` first to confirm.

Example:
    bin/rails g rls_policy posts

    This will create:
        db/migrate/<timestamp>_add_rls_policies_for_posts.rb

    After generation:
        bin/rails db:migrate
        bin/rake validator:lint_schema  # should show <n>/<n>/<n> aligned

See also:
    - docs/architecture/data-version.md (双保险 section)
    - docs/decisions/ADR-014-rls-policy-generator.md
